speaker: VK
words: Rectoral election. After a great deal of plotting and scheming Reuther was elected for the second time and Gehrig was defeated.
It was a dirty business; they pulled a fast one on our section.
Despite my participation in the “Whispering Committee” I felt inwardly almost unmoved.
It bothered me just as little that yesterday evening (section meeting) Beste became dean.
Old French to six, cultural history to about twenty, the seminar to ten people.
But, in compliance with the “request” from the rectorship, I don’t examine. I did not attend the section meeting either.
